Rating: 3
This is a good base recipe but some might like to try these changes/additions. Brown the meat first, remove beef and the grease from the pan. Brown onions first in olive oil, when they soften add sliced fresh mushrooms, bell pepper if you like, add the garlic last so it doesn't burn. Instead of tomato paste and sauce, try equal amounts (more or less) of ketchup and water. Season with salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, jerk seasonings, southwestern seasonings or whatever you like. Add the beef back to the pan and simmer, simmer, simmer. The flavors intensify as time goes on.

