Rating: 4
To the guy who claims this dish is in reality Cuban Picadillo. Your history of the dish is probably accurate. However given that this dish is not called "picadillo," and given that most Americans are not in Havana, Cuba, and given that the original Havana bar call Sloppy Joes probably doesn't even exist any longer, thanks to Senior Castro. I doubt this was ever intended to be authentic Cuban Picadillo. Now, you can go right ahead and do whatever you want to do to any Cuban that makes this recipe. However for us Americans who love American(ized)"Sloppy Joe" sandwiches this recipe is great, and probably a heck of a lot better than the original.

Rating: 4
