Rating: 0
During the Thirties, a bar by the wharfs in Havana, Cuba, introduced to foreign sailors what was a famous cuban dish: "picadillo". Since the name of the bar was "The Sloppy Joe" the dish took that name outside of Cuba. By the way, Sloppy Joe is, today, the name of a bar in Key West,Florida, but the original was the one in Havana. Anyhow, no picadillo or sloppy joe was ever cooked in Cuba using: celery, jalapeno pepper, ketchup, tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Any cook guilty of doing so would have been drowned in Havana harbor. Wrong recipe. Gets a Big O from me or any other cuban.

